    <item>
      <title>Time Arithmetic with Date and Time in Ruby</title>
      <link>https://yegorov.github.io/notes/time-arithmetic-with-date-and-time-in-ruby/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 16 Jun 2026 08:06:24 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://yegorov.github.io/notes/time-arithmetic-with-date-and-time-in-ruby/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;What I enjoy most in Ruby is working with &lt;a href=&#34;https://docs.ruby-lang.org/en/master/Date.html#method-i-2B&#34;  class=&#34;external-link&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;date&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&#34;https://docs.ruby-lang.org/en/master/Time.html#method-i-2B&#34;  class=&#34;external-link&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;time&lt;/a&gt; objects.&#xA;The standard library implements time arithmetic especially elegantly: adding and subtracting seconds, days, and months.&#xA;I&amp;rsquo;ve never seen anything like this in any other language, where it looks so clear, concise, and beautiful:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-ruby&#34; data-lang=&#34;ruby&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nb&#34;&gt;require&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;s1&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;time&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;now&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;no&#34;&gt;Time&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;now&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;now&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;+&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;mi&#34;&gt;20&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;c1&#34;&gt;# 20 seconds from now&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;now&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;mi&#34;&gt;20&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;c1&#34;&gt;# 20 seconds ago&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;date&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;no&#34;&gt;Time&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;now&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;to_date&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;date&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;+&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;mi&#34;&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;  &lt;span class=&#34;c1&#34;&gt;# 3 days from now&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;date&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;mi&#34;&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;  &lt;span class=&#34;c1&#34;&gt;# 3 days ago&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;date&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;mi&#34;&gt;6&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;c1&#34;&gt;# 6 months from now&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;date&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;mi&#34;&gt;6&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;c1&#34;&gt;# 6 months ago&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;And ActiveSupport only enhances this impression with an additional &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/rails/rails/blob/main/activesupport/lib/active_support/duration.rb&#34;  class=&#34;external-link&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;Duration&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt; class, making working with time and dates even more pleasant:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
